  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Les Bruyeres is on a half board basis.</p>
<p>Each morning a continental buffet breakfast with additional hot options is served between 7 - 10 am </p>
<p>When you return from a day on the slopes you can enjoy a three-course meal. Starters and desserts are available from the buffet and the main course is served. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Les Bruyeres is located at the foot of the slopes, next to the Les Bruyeres ski lifts - giving you convenient access to the extensive <a data-udi="umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578" href="/{localLink:umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578}" title="Three Valleys Ski Area">Three Valleys Ski Area</a>. And after a day of skiing, you can enjoy a drink on the sun terrace with incredible views or relax in the wellness area included with your stay.</p>
<h2>Great location</h2>
<p>Located in the centre of the Bruyeres village, you really couldn't ask for a hotel with better access to the surrounding facilities and slopes. The Les Bruyeres lift is just next door, and you can ski back to the hotel at the end of the day, making this a great option for the keen skiers and snowboarders. </p>
<h2>Relax and unwind </h2>
<p>After a day of skiing the Three Valleys, make the most of the hotels own wellness area featuring a relaxation area, sauna and hammam and if relaxing isn't for you head into the fitness room which has a range of equipment - entry is free of charge for guests. For the ultimate treat book a massage or beauty treatment in the spa area. The hotel has panoramic mountain views from the sun terrace, it is an excellent spot to enjoy a cocktail and soak up the winter sun, or cosy up in the lounge with a vin chaud (hot wine) with a book in front of the open fireplace - there is even live music throughout the winter season to keep you entertained.</p>
<p>Each day you can enjoy a buffet style breakfast with a variety of options, and when you return from a day on the slopes an extensive buffet style meal awaits you - plus each week you can sample some of the local cuisine at the Savoyard evening. </p>]]></description>
